Alternatives

     Alternatives to ad-supported websites, software, and publications.

Communication

     * [https://www.fastmail.com/]FastMail - Reliable business email with
       no data lock-in.
     * [https://jitsi.org/jitsi-meet/]Jitsi Meet - Secure video
       conferencing and desktop sharing using WebRTC.
     * [https://protonmail.com/]ProtonMail - Free encrypted email.
     * [https://ring.cx/]Ring - Telephone, teleconferencing, and media
       sharing through a distributed service.
     * [https://www.whispersystems.org/]Signal - Private messaging and
       calling for desktop, Android, and iOS.
     * [https://telegram.org/]Telegram - Cloud-based mobile and desktop
       messaging app with a focus on security and speed.
     * [https://tox.chat/]Tox - Encrypted and distributed messaging
       platform with voice, video, and screen sharing.
     * [https://wire.com/en/privacy/]Wire - Text, audio, and video
       communication with end-to-end encryption.
     * [https://write.as/principles]Write.as - Blogging platform that
       allows you to publish ideas without distraction.

File Sharing

     * [https://justimg.chaoswebs.net/]JustIMG - Simple image host with no
       tracking.
     * [https://mega.nz/]Mega - 50 GB of secure free storage. Files are
       encrypted client-side.
     * [https://www.qbittorrent.org/]qBittorrent - Free and open source
       BitTorrent client.

Mobile Apps

     * [https://github.com/arpitkh96/AmazeFileManager]Amaze File Manager -
       Open source, Material Design file explorer for Android devices.
     * [https://www.bible.com/]Bible - Bible reader with many versions and
       languages to choose from.
     * [https://readytheapp.com/]Ready - Minimalist news reader for iOS.

Music

     * [https://libre.fm/]Libre.fm - Stream, download, remix, and share
       music for free.
     * [http://mstream.io/]mStream - Suite of software for syncing and
       streaming music across multiple devices.
     * [https://voltra.co/]Voltra - DRM-free music listening and discovery
       software that supports artists directly.

Publications

     * [https://www.adbusters.org/]Adbusters - Magazine about the takeover
       of psychological, physical, and cultural environments by commercial
       forces.
     * [https://aeon.co/]Aeon - Digital magazine that publishes original
       thinking on science, philosophy, society, and the arts.
     * [https://www.armstrongeconomics.com/uncategorized/no-advertising/]A
       rmstrong Economics - Educational blog about markets and the global
       economy.
     * [https://www.commondreams.org/]Common Dreams - Progressive news
       website.
     * [https://consumerist.com/]Consumerist - Independent source of
       consumer news and information.
     * [https://ello.co/]Ello - Media platform for creators and artists
       that does not sell user data.
     * [https://popularresistance.org/]Popular Resistance - Independent,
       nonviolent, and diverse movements to end the power of concentrated
       wealth and put human needs before corporate greed.
     * [https://realsport101.com/]RealSport - Fans write articles on
       football, basketball, cricket, e-sports, motorsports, and most
       other sports out there. This site is committed to maintaining an
       experience free of pop-ups, fake news, click-bait, and ads.
     * [https://theconversation.com/]The Conversation - High quality,
       authenticated, explanatory journalism funded by universities.

Reference

     * [https://www.openstreetmap.org/]OpenStreetMap - Map of the world
       created by users and released under an open license.
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page]Wikipedia - Encyclopedia
       that anyone can edit.
     * [https://www.wiktionary.org/]Wiktionary - Dictionary that anyone
       can edit.
     * [http://www.weather.gov/]Weather.gov - Weather reports for places
       in the United States.

Social

     * [https://gnusocial.no/]GNUsocial.no - Allows users to connect and
       share with each other; expenses are covered by donations.
     * [https://lobste.rs/]Lobsters - Simple link aggregation site with
       explanations required to downvote.
     * [https://mastodon.social/]Mastodon - Free, open source, and
       decentralized social network server.
     * [https://quitter.se/]Quitter.se - Twitter clone that is part of the
       federated GNU social network.

Utilities

     * [https://etherpad.wikimedia.org/]Etherpad - Collaborative document
       editing in real-time.
     * [https://www.protectedtext.com/]ProtectedText - Online encrypted
       notepad with storage and no sign up.
     * [https://www.taskade.com/]Taskade - Collaborative task lists and
       outlines.

Video

     * [https://goblinrefuge.com/mediagoblin/]Goblin Refuge - Video and
       image sharing service powered by MediaGoblin.
     * [https://popchest.com/]PopChest - Upcoming video platform that
       gives creators financial freedom.
     * [https://vimeo.com/]Vimeo - Alternative to YouTube for viewing and
       uploading videos.

Resources

Ad Blockers

     * [https://add-art.org/]Add-Art - Replaces ads with art.
     * [https://github.com/gorhill/uBlock]uBlock Origin - General-purpose
       blocker that removes ads and privacy-invading trackers by default.

   Note: Avoid Adblock Plus because coprorations can
   [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adblock_Plus#Controversy_over_ad_filteri
   ng_and_ad_whitelisting]pay to have their ads whitelisted and uBlock
   (unrelated to the project above) because it solicits excessive
   donations and has what could be considered "ads" on its own site.

Articles

     * [https://zenhabits.net/opt-out/]A Call for Revolt: Advertising is
       the Anti-Minimalism - Opt-out of the advertising game.
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anti-consumerism]Anti-Consumerism on
       Wikipedia - Overview of the sociopolitical ideology that opposes
       consumerism.
     * [https://www.stevepavlina.com/blog/2011/12/conscious-success/]Consc
       ious Success - Explores the idea of conscious success rather than
       accidental success, using ads as an example.
     * [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Criticism_of_advertising]Criticism
       of Advertising on Wikipedia - Overview of common criticisms of
       advertising.
     * [https://www.stevepavlina.com/blog/2008/10/dropping-adsense-saying-
       goodbye-to-100k-per-year-in-easy-income/]Saying Goodbye to $100K
       Per Year in Easy Income - Story of a blogger who chose a better way
       to make a living.
     * [http://practicaltypography.com/vote-with-your-wallet.html]Vote
       With Your Wallet, Not Your Ad Blocker - Paying for ad-free services
       casts a bigger vote.

Businesses

     These business have no advertising policies.

     * [https://www.gandi.net/]Gandi - Domain registrar with a No Bullshit
       policy.
     * [https://www.kakulas.com.au/who-we-are/no-advertising/]Kakulas
       Legal - Law firm that you won't find in the yellow pages.
     * [http://www.polyfacefarms.com/no-advertising/]Polyface Farms -
       Environmentally-friendly farm that relies on word of mouth to reach
       customers.

Groups

     * [http://adfreeblog.org/]Ad Free Blog - Icons for showing opposition
       to the use of corporate advertising on blogs.
     * [https://antiadvertisingagency.com/our-mission/]Anti-Advertising
       Agency - Calls into question the purpose and effects of advertising
       in public space.
     * [http://artnotads.org/]Art Not Ads - Artists creating change in the
       urban landscape, but not by going after the ads themselves.
     * [http://brandalism.ch/]Brandalism - International street art
       collective that subverts advertising in urban space.
     * [http://banbillboardblight.org/]Coalition to Ban Billboard Blight -
       Defending the urban landscape of Los Angeles from a proliferation
       of billboards.
     * [http://no-ads.ca/]Digital Public Library Project - Promotes a
       Digital Public Library system that can replace advertising funded
       media.
     * [https://www.nomoreads.org/]No More Ads - Manifesto promoting an
       ad-free internet.

Make Money Without Ads

     * [https://flattr.com/]Flattr - Browser add-on that distributes a
       monthly budget to websites you engage with the most.
     * [https://liberapay.com/]Liberapay - Open source recurring donations
       platform.
     * [https://opencollective.com/]OpenCollective - Enables groups to set
       up a collective, raise funds, and manage them transparently.
     * [https://www.patreon.com/]Patreon - Recurring funding for artists
       and creators on either a monthly basis or per creation.

Talks

     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=01PUSrLCvcM]What if there was no
       advertising?

